

=Examples=

* FinalsClub: Free site for sharing Harvard University course notes that plans to expand to other elite universities
* GradeGuru: The note-sharing site is run by a major textbook publisher, McGraw-Hill Education, and pays students small rewards—in cash or gift cards—based on the popularity of their notes. The site makes all of the notes free to visitors.
* Mixable: Lets students share notes and coursework as well as form study groups within Facebook, using a free application developed at Purdue University.


